I have a Console application that targets .NET Core 2.1 in which I make an HTTP/2 request to google. However, when I inspect the outgoing HTTP request, I notice that the request was downgraded to HTTP/1.1. This can also be verified by checking the Version of the response.

```C#
var client = new HttpClient();

var req = new HttpRequestMessage(HttpMethod.Get, "https://www.google.com")
{
      Version = new Version(2, 0)
};

var x = client.SendAsync(req);

var version = x.Result.Version; // 1.1
```

If I target .NET Core 2.0 or earlier, the HTTP/2 header is not altered.

Is this a known issue? Does anyone have any insight into this problem?

For the record, this is a problem on both Windows and Mac.

Thanks!


